<h3>Question 10</h3>
<div><p><p>What is the advantage of real time rendering over offline rendering? Discuss the limitation of Z-Buffer algorithm.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><div class="table_wrapper" style="overflow-x:auto;"><table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 240px;">
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 24px;">
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;"><strong>Real Time Rendering</strong></td>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;"><strong>Offline Rendering</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 24px;">
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">Takes short period of time.</td>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">Takes longer time.</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 24px;">
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">More performance-critical.</td>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">Much less performance-critical.</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 24px;">
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">Less expensive.</td>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">You have to use very expensive rendering techniques.</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 120px;">
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 120px;"> Is calculated at the instant you ask for your whatever solution to generate the images</td>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 120px;"> Is not submitted to the time constraint. Basically a scene is prepared and then a series of pictures is generated (&#8220;pre-calculated&#8221;) and ultimately assembled into a sort of a video clip that then is viewed (&#8220;off line&#8221;).</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 24px;">
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">A realtime rendering situation needs to get everything done in a fraction of a second so it can keep up with user input.</td>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">Offline rendering can take as long as you like per frame (limited only by your patience), as it doesn&#8217;t need to keep up with any inputs.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p><strong>Limitations of Z Buffer:</strong></p>
<p>Requires an additional buffer.</p>
<p>Requires large memory.</p>
<p>Time consuming process.</p>
</div>
